snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve had a similar experience with the tablets before. I was at the doctors with a bunch of illnesses, and I had to be MRI scanned. The doctors wanted to sent me to LONDON so I could me anaesthetised by a professional so I’d be asleep. I said no, I’m not taking 3 hours of trains for 1 30-minute scan, so the doctors said I could it with a sedative at the hospital we were at.

Unfortunately, not only do I fight sedatives subconsciously, like my mum does, but I also managed to WAKE UP after about 5 minutes, on the trolley to the MRI machine. So in the end, I did the entire scan awake, just keeping still. It wasn’t that scary though luckily, and somehow we only had to repeat one small section of the scan due to me being unable to sit still.

snippet.textDisplay: When I got my wisdom teeth out, I didn’t get a video, a meeting, a mouth guard, or glasses.They gave me gas and two shots on both sides of my mouth for all four of my teeth as well as the roof of my mouth to numb my throat. They practicality broke my jaw open and removed the teeth but the last one they removed was the first one they numbed so it wore off and I FELT IT and what’s worse is that it was the hardest to remove and the had to cut it into three pieces. I was very conscious and they were even talking to me while I did it. I also didn’t get stitches so it took a month and a half to heal and I also have a good bit of trauma now. I don’t trust elderly dentists anymore.

However, last month my half broken tooth starting aching & didn’t want to go back to that place again so my sister recommended a private clinic and the dentist was actually doing a great job but my parents weren’t happy cuz now I have to pay for every appointment and I have a lot to fix cuz the previous dentists did a wacky job trying to “fix” my teeth it was so obvious that they weren’t doing good at their job but my parents wanted me to keep going there anyways since it’s free. Anyways I’m so glad I’m fixing my teethes properly now but cuz of the horrible past experiences whenever I go to the dentist now I keep freaking out & I cried twice while getting my tooth treated because of anxiety

snippet.textDisplay: GIRL! When went to get my wisdom teeth out I totally panicked. They did the same do me as they did to you, some medicine so I would chill, but nothing to knock me out. I ended up crying and shaking so much the dentist decided it was too risky to continue. Btw, I had 5 (five)(I'm not bullshiting you, five) (I have proof) wisdom teeth. 4 and a little one that was too close to a thing that if damaged could paralyze half of my face, maybe for ever. With all those risks the dentist decided to do the procedure with total anesthesia, 100% blacked out. That envolves many risks as well but boy, I wasn't ready. One of the things he used over heated and burnt the right side of my under lip. Second degree burn. I left the hospital the next day with a gigantic face and a gigantic burnt lip, for the next 2 weeks I couldn't eat properly, for the next month or so I had to use a mask to go to college because otherwise the burn could be exposed to infections, and only another month later it closed. It's been a year now, and I have a red scar under my lip. Bit traumatic, never going under a surgery again, unless it is a life or death situation. (English isn't my first language, be patient about the grammar, plz)
